        {
          "id": "sol-1-1",
          "courseId": "rust-solana",
          "order": 1,
          "type": "concept",
          "title": {
            "EN": "Accounts Model vs EVM",
            "ES": "Modelo de Cuentas vs EVM"
          },
          "content": {
            "EN": "# Stateless Programs\nIn Ethereum, contracts hold both code and state (storage variables).\nIn Solana, **Programs are stateless**. They are just logic (code).\nState is stored in separate **Data Accounts**.\n*   When you call a program, you must pass all the accounts it needs to read or write to.\n*   This allows the runtime (Sealevel) to execute transactions in **Parallel**, because it knows exactly which memory regions (accounts) each transaction touches. If Tx A touches Account 1 and Tx B touches Account 2, they run simultaneously on different CPU cores.",
            "ES": "# Programas Sin Estado\nEn Ethereum, los contratos tienen código y estado.\nEn Solana, **los Programas son stateless**. Solo lógica.\nEl estado vive en **Cuentas de Datos** separadas.\n*   Al llamar un programa, pasas todas las cuentas que necesita.\n*   Esto permite al runtime (Sealevel) ejecutar transacciones en **Paralelo**."
          }
        },
        {
